title.narrative: 3.1. FULL DEVELOPMENT IN EARLY CHILDHOOD

description.narrative: By 2021, the capacity of the State and society for the coordinated design and management of equitable and relevant policies for full development in early childhood (0â€“5 years) in the priority territories will have been built., which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Birth Registration, Child Health, Early Detection And Treatment Of Malnutrition, Early Learning, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence (Covid), Health Systems Strengthening, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Infant And Young Child Feeding, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Maternal And Newborn Health, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition And Emergencies, Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Social Protection And Child Poverty, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, children exposed to concerns related to gender, ethnicity, area of residence, living conditions or differences in skills will live in safe environments and have full access to relevant and quality registration, health, nutrition, care, education, water, sanitation and hygiene services that promote their full development.

title.narrative: By 2021, the capacity of the State and society for the coordinated design and management of equitable and relevant policies forfull development in early childhood (0?5 years) in the priority territories will have been built.

description.narrative: In a year marked by the pandemic UNICEF contributed to continuity of Early Childhood Development (ECD) services, institutionalizing a comprehensive model, developing guidelinesandan innovative virtual monitoring platform. UNICEF reached 12,000 children and 14,000 families with an integral package to ensure health, education, and protection services. UNICEFsupported the identification andcare of children with development delays/ disabilities (with new tools, training, and pilots), andpositioned relevant emerging issues,such as mental health, overweight and obesity into public agenda. UNICEF supported the promotion of the government vaccination strategy against COVID-19, facilitated cold chain procurement andtransport,and developed materials and communication campaigns, with focus on indigenous communities. | Status:Met | As-of Date:17/12/2021
